commit.message:
release 3.14

Addresses issue #74

Update README.md

shell syntax highlighting added

fix stale url showing latest changes

* ps_mem.py: Update to dedicated repo.
Also update to https.
Fixes issue #71

make recent change compat with python2

Use python2 compat form of super()

python-3.6 flush check raises ret_code 120

Since python 3.6, output is sanitized during interpreter exit.
Because Unbuffered() inherits from 'object', not every method from
TextIOBase is implemented and this causes python setting return
code to 120.
This was spotted in our CI and is a common issue with IO wrappers
inheriting from simple 'object'.

(Python maintainer stated that the previous implementation might
have always failed, but it was not sanitized until python-3.6.)

fix accounting of huge pages

account for huge pages separately,
as the kernel doesn't include these values in RSS or PSS,
for some reason.

We add Private_Hugetlb to private memory,
but only after PSS calculations have been done.
We also propagate Shared_Hugetlb separately,
and add the largest for each command to the command total.
We may overestimate shared mem usage if shared huge pages
are shared across separate commands.

Fixes issue #64

move from getopt to argparse

While both are in the python stdlib,
argparse is the recommended one
as it's more aligned with python,
and results in less code

group process trees with the same executable

Previously "Web Content" was separated from "firefox" for example,
even though these all had the same /usr/lib.../firefox exe.

Note we don't always just group by exe as that would mean
all python processes would be grouped for example.

commit.message:
fix erroneous warning about missing swap info

Fixes issue #38

support python-2.4

I got a request to maintain support for RHEL 5,
so since it's easy, let's continue to do so.

use /proc/$pid/smaps_rollup where available

This is a more efficient equivalent to /proc/$pid/smaps
See: https://marc.info/?l=linux-mm&m=150250453624272&w=2

Fixes issue #33

only show a single swap value with --swap

This just shows SwapPss or if not available, Swap.

That will fixes as a side effect the missing "Shared Swap"
header when using --swap.

Also support --total with --swap.

Also report accuracy issues with --swap.

Fixes issue #34
bump release number for recent changes

handle new line in arguments with --split-args

replace with spaces

Fixes issue #29

allow running as normal user when specifying pids

Fixes issue #28

Add Swap support as an option:

-S | --swap  To show swap information of each program and the total
             swap. It is recovered from /proc/<pid>/smaps. Also, if
             the kernel supports SwapPss, it prints the Shared Swap
             information of each Program (Note that Swap - SwapPss
             is not Private Swap) and the total of Shared Swap.

-d | --discriminate-by-pid  Discriminate by process id, and do not
                            group by program.

flush stdout when repeating output with -w

Avoid needing to use stdbuf when piping ps_mem output.
We flush by default, as the amount of data output is small
relative to the associated processing, and so performance
will not be significantly affected.

This command will now output immediately:

  $ sudo ps_mem -t -w 1 | cat

run pyflakes on Travis using tox

Use tox 1.x compatible environments by default
document install methods

remove yocto package

This was out of date with downstream package files,
and since we don't have any other distro files within
the ps_mem, it's most consistent to just remove.
